Developments in science and technology have significantly shaped human history by transforming how people live and interact. Innovations such as telephones, the Internet, and engines have facilitated faster communication and transportation, allowing for the rapid exchange of ideas and goods. These advancements have led to modernization and civilization, enabling societies to evolve and adapt over time. Additionally, improvements in tools and agricultural techniques have resulted in food surpluses, which allowed populations to grow and diversify their occupations beyond farming.